The paper deals with computational lower bounds for high-dimensional statistics problems, which typically involve large amounts of data and structured signals in noise. This suggests that the paper may belong to the categories of cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses information-theoretic limits, which could place it in the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper introduces new techniques for average-case reductions, which could be relevant to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
